100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 21, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, grappling with the ongoing challenges of international security and disarmament. In the U.S., the Supreme Court ruled on the controversial case of the "Scottsboro Boys," setting a significant precedent for civil rights in the legal system. Meanwhile, in Berlin, tensions rose as political factions clashed over the future of the Weimar Republic, reflecting the growing instability in post-war Germany.
